==Events == * [[694]] &ndash; [[Egica]], a king of the [[Visigoths]] of [[Hispania]], accuses [[Jew]]s of aiding [[Muslim]]s, sentencing all Jews to [[slavery]]. *[[1282]] &ndash; [[Pope Martin IV]] excommunicates King [[Peter III of Aragon]]. *[[1313]] &ndash; [[Louis the Bavarian]] defeats his cousin [[Frederick I of Austria (Habsburg)|Frederick I of Austria]] at the [[Battle of Gamelsdorf]]. *[[1330]] &ndash; [[Battle of Posada]], Wallachian Voievode [[Basarab I]] defeats the [[Hungary|Hungarian]] army in an ambush *[[1456]] &ndash; [[Ulrich II of Celje]] ([[Slovene language|Slovene]]: Ulrik Celjski, [[German language|German]] Ulrich von Cilli, [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]]: Cillei Ulrik), last [[prince]] of [[Celje]] [[principality]], is assassinated in [[Belgrade]]. *[[1492]] &ndash; [[Peace of Etaples]] between [[Henry VII of England|Henry VII]] and [[Charles VIII of France|Charles VIII]]. *[[1494]] &ndash; The [[Family de' Medici]] are expelled from [[Florence]]. *[[1520]] &ndash; More than 50 people are sentenced and executed in the [[Stockholm Bloodbath]] *[[1620]] &ndash; [[Pilgrim (Plymouth Colony)|Pilgrim]]s aboard the ''[[Mayflower]]'' sight land at [[Cape Cod]], [[Massachusetts]]. *[[1688]] &ndash; The [[Glorious Revolution]]: [[William III of England|William of Orange]] captures [[Exeter]]. *[[1697]] &ndash; [[Pope Innocent XII]] founds the city of [[Cervia]]. *[[1720]] &ndash; The synagogue of [[Judah he-Hasid (Jerusalem)|Yehudah he-Hasid]] is burned down by Arab creditors, leading to the expulsion of the [[Ashkenazi Jews|Ashkenazim]] from [[Jerusalem]]. *[[1729]] &ndash; [[Spain]], [[France]] and [[Great Britain]] sign the [[Treaty of Seville]]. *[[1764]] &ndash; [[Mary Campbell (colonial settler)|Mary Campbell]], a captive of the [[Lenape]] during the [[French and Indian War]], is turned over to forces commanded by Colonel [[Henry Bouquet]]. *[[1780]] &ndash; [[American Revolutionary War]]: In the [[Battle of Fishdam Ford]] a force British and Loyalist troops fail in a surprise attack against the [[South Carolina]] Patriot militia under Brigadier General [[Thomas Sumter]]. *[[1791]] &ndash; Foundation of the Dublin [[Society of United Irishmen]]. *[[1793]] &ndash; [[William Carey (missionary)|William Carey]] reaches the [[Hooghly River]]. *[[1799]] &ndash; [[Napoleon I of France|Napoleon Bonaparte]] leads the [[Coup d'Ã©tat]] of [[18 Brumaire]] ending the [[French Directory|Directory]] government, and becoming one of its three Consuls ([[French Consulate|Consulate Government]]). *[[1822]] &ndash; The [[Action of 9 November 1822]] between {{USS|Alligator|1820|6}} and a squadron of [[pirate|piratical]] [[schooner]]s off the coast of [[Cuba]]. *[[1848]] &ndash; [[Robert Blum]], a [[Germany|German]] revolutionary, is executed in [[Vienna]]. *[[1851]] &ndash; [[Kentucky]] marshals abduct abolitionist minister [[Calvin Fairbank]] from [[Jeffersonville, Indiana]], and take him to Kentucky to stand trial for helping a [[slave]] escape. *[[1857]] &ndash; [[The Atlantic]] founded in [[Boston]]. *[[1861]] &ndash; The first documented [[Canadian Football|football]] match in [[Canada]] is played at [[University College, University of Toronto]]. *[[1862]] &ndash; [[American Civil War]]: [[United States|Union]] General [[Ambrose Burnside]] assumes command of the [[Army of the Potomac]], after [[George B. McClellan]] is removed. *[[1867]] &ndash; [[Tokugawa Shogunate]] hands power back to the Emperor of [[Japan]], starting the [[Meiji Restoration]]. *[[1872]] &ndash; The [[Great Boston Fire of 1872]]. *[[1887]] &ndash; The [[United States]] receives rights to [[Pearl Harbor, Hawaii]]. *[[1888]] &ndash; [[Jack the Ripper]] kills [[Mary Jane Kelly]], his last known victim. *[[1906]] &ndash; [[Theodore Roosevelt]] is the first sitting [[President of the United States]] to make an official trip outside the country. He did so to inspect progress on the [[Panama Canal]]. *[[1907]] &ndash; The [[Cullinan Diamond]] is presented to [[Edward VII of the United Kingdom|King Edward VII]] on his birthday. *[[1913]] &ndash; The [[Great Lakes Storm of 1913]], the most destructive natural disaster ever to hit the lakes, destroys 19 ships and kills more than 250 people. *[[1914]] &ndash; [[SMS Emden (1908)|SMS ''Emden'']] sunk by {{HMAS|Sydney|1912|6}} in the [[Battle of Cocos]]. *[[1917]] &ndash; [[Joseph Stalin]] enters the provisional government of Bolshevik Russia. *[[1918]] &ndash; [[Kaiser]] [[Wilhelm II of Germany]] abdicates after the [[German Revolution of 1918â1919|German Revolution]], and [[Germany]] is proclaimed a [[Republic]]. *[[1923]] &ndash; In [[Munich, Germany]], police and government troops crush the [[Beer Hall Putsch]] in [[Bavaria]]. The failed [[coup]] is the work of the [[Nazis]]. *[[1935]] &ndash; The [[Congress of Industrial Organizations]] is founded in [[Atlantic City, New Jersey]] by eight [[trade unions]] belonging to the [[American Federation of Labor]]. *[[1937]] &ndash; [[Japan]]ese troops take control of [[Shanghai, China]]. *[[1938]] &ndash; Nazi German diplomat [[Ernst vom Rath]] dies from the fatal gunshot wounds of Jewish resistance fighter [[Herschel Grynszpan]], an act which the Nazis used as an excuse to instigate the 1938 national [[pogrom]], also known as [[Kristallnacht]]. *[[1940]] &ndash; [[Warsaw]] is awarded the [[Virtuti Militari]]. *[[1947]] &ndash; India [[Indian integration of Junagadh|forcibly annexes]] [[Junagadh]] from Pakistan. *[[1953]] &ndash; [[Cambodia]] becomes independent from [[France]]. *[[1960]] &ndash; [[Robert McNamara]] is named president of [[Ford Motor Co.]], the first non-Ford to serve in that post. A month later, he quit to join the newly-elected [[John F. Kennedy]] administration. *[[1963]] &ndash; At [[Miike coal mine]], [[Miike District, Fukuoka|Miike]], [[Japan]], an explosion kills 458, and hospitalises 839 with [[carbon monoxide poisoning]]. *[[1965]] &ndash; Several [[U.S. state]]s and parts of [[Canada]] are hit by a series of [[Power outage|blackout]]s lasting up to 13 hours in the [[Northeast Blackout of 1965]]. * 1965 &ndash; [[Catholic Worker]] member [[Roger Allen LaPorte]], protesting against the [[Vietnam War]], sets himself on [[fire]] in front of the [[United Nations]] building. *[[1967]] &ndash; [[Apollo program]]: [[NASA]] launches the unmanned [[Apollo 4]] test spacecraft atop the first [[Saturn V]] rocket from [[Cape Kennedy, Florida]]. * 1967 &ndash; First issue of [[Rolling Stone]] Magazine is published. *[[1970]] &ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: The [[Supreme Court of the United States]] votes 6 to 3 against hearing a case to allow [[Massachusetts]] to enforce its [[law]] granting residents the right to refuse military service in an undeclared [[war]]. *[[1979]] &ndash; [[Nuclear weapon|Nuclear]] [[false alarm]]: the [[NORAD]] computers and the Alternate National Military Command Center in [[Fort Ritchie, Maryland]] detected purported massive [[Soviet]] nuclear strike. After reviewing the raw data from satellites and checking the [[early warning]] radars, the alert is cancelled. *[[1985]] &ndash; [[Garry Kasparov]], 22, of the [[Soviet Union]] becomes the youngest [[World Chess Champion]] by beating [[Anatoly Karpov]], also of the Soviet Union. *[[1989]] &ndash; [[Cold War]]: [[Berlin Wall|Fall of the Berlin Wall]]. [[Communism|Communist]]-controlled [[East Germany]] opens [[Border checkpoint|checkpoint]]s in the Berlin Wall allowing its citizens to travel to [[West Germany]]. This key event led to the eventual [[German reunification|reunification of East and West Germany]]. *[[1993]] &ndash; [[Stari most]], the "old bridge" in [[Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnia]]n [[Mostar]] built in [[1566]], collapses after several days of bombing. *[[1994]] &ndash; The [[chemical element]] [[Darmstadtium]] is discovered. *[[1998]] &ndash; A US federal judge ordered 37 US brokerage houses to pay 1.03 billion [[United States dollar|USD]] to cheated [[NASDAQ]] investors to compensate for [[price-fixing]]. This is the largest civil settlement in [[United States]] history. * 1998 &ndash; [[Capital punishment in the United Kingdom]], already abolished for [[murder]], is completely abolished for all remaining capital offences. *[[2005]] &ndash; The [[Venus Express]] mission of the [[European Space Agency]] is launched from the [[Baikonur Cosmodrome]] in [[Kazakhstan]]. * 2005 &ndash; [[2005 Amman bombings|Suicide bombers attacked]] three hotels in [[Amman, Jordan]], killing at least 60 people. *[[2007]] &ndash; The German [[Bundestag]] passes the controversial [[Telecommunications data retention|data retention bill]] mandating storage of citizens' telecommunications traffic data for six months without [[probable cause]].
